{"closingIssuesReferences":[],"files":[{"path":"README.md","additions":87,"deletions":0,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"dream-mobile.sh","additions":38,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/.gitignore","additions":1,"deletions":0,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"dream-server/README.md","additions":58,"deletions":1,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"dream-server/docs/IOS-ASHELL-SHORTCUTS.md","additions":62,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/docs/IOS-ASHELL-WASM-RUNTIME.md","additions":84,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/docs/MOBILE-SHELL-QUICKSTART.md","additions":154,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/docs/PLATFORM-TRUTH-TABLE.md","additions":7,"deletions":1,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"dream-server/docs/SUPPORT-MATRIX.md","additions":8,"deletions":2,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"dream-server/dream-mobile.sh","additions":341,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/install.sh","additions":37,"deletions":1,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/common.sh","additions":26,"deletions":1,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/dispatch.sh","additions":3,"deletions":0,"changeType":"MODIFIED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/android-local-server.py","additions":1645,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/android-local-ui/app.css","additions":1027,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/android-local-ui/app.js","additions":880,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/android-local-ui/index.html","additions":372,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/build-ios-ashell-wasm-runtime.sh","additions":261,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/build-ios-ashell-wasm-sdk.sh","additions":203,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/install-mobile.sh","additions":415,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/ios-ashell-cli.sh","additions":113,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/ios-ashell-install.sh","additions":313,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/ios-wasm-runner/CMakeLists.txt","additions":45,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/ios-wasm-runner/__cpp_exception.S","additions":10,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/ios-wasm-runner/dlfcn_stubs.cpp","additions":22,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/installers/mobile/ios-wasm-runner/main.cpp","additions":587,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/mobile-runtime/ios-ashell/bin/llama-cli.wasm","additions":0,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/tests/bats-tests/dispatch.bats","additions":60,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"dream-server/tests/smoke/mobile-dispatch.sh","additions":22,"deletions":0,"changeType":"ADDED"},{"path":"install.sh","additions":10,"deletions":20,"changeType":"MODIFIED"}],"reviewDecision":"CHANGES_REQUESTED","reviewRequests":[],"reviews":[{"id":"PRR_kwDORMI4oM72b1fu","author":{"login":"Lightheartdevs"},"authorAssociation":"MEMBER","body":"Appreciate the ambition and the scope discipline on docs — the mobile preview paths are clearly marked as beta and the detection gating is thoughtful. But this is too big and too risky to land as a single PR from a first-time contributor.\n\n**Blocking concerns:**\n\n1. **Scope**: 6,891 additions spanning Android (Python server + HTML/CSS/JS UI), iOS (C++ WASM runner + build scripts), a new dispatcher wrapper, new docs, and tests. This is three separate product bets in one PR:\n   - Android Termux path (Python server + localhost UI)\n   - iOS a-Shell WASM path (C++ runtime build + prebuilt binary)\n   - Installer dispatcher refactor touching desktop install.sh\n\n2. **Committed binary artifact**: `dream-server/mobile-runtime/ios-ashell/bin/llama-cli.wasm` is checked in (additions:0, deletions:0 — so it's a binary blob counted outside the diff stats). Binaries in git are a reproducibility and supply-chain concern. Options:\n   - Build it in CI from the included `ios-wasm-runner/` C++ source, commit SHA256 only.\n   - Host it as a GitHub Release artifact, have the installer fetch it at install time with SHA check.\n   - Git LFS if you really want it in the repo (but still not ideal).\n   The current state — a binary nobody but the author can reproduce — shouldn't ship.\n\n3. **Desktop install.sh shebang change**: `#!/bin/bash` → `#!/bin/sh` with re-exec to bash. The re-exec logic looks correct, but changing the shebang on the primary install entrypoint for every user to support iOS is the tail wagging the dog. Consider a separate `install-mobile.sh` entrypoint documented in the README, leave desktop install.sh alone.\n\n4. **Platform detection false-positive surface**: `ASHELL` env var, `TERM_PROGRAM==a-Shell`, and the `/var/mobile/Containers/Data/Application` path matcher. If any desktop user has `ASHELL` set for an unrelated reason, they get routed to the mobile installer. Unlikely but not impossible — a stricter multi-signal gate would reduce risk.\n\n5. **Maintenance surface**: Android Python server is 1,645 lines, Android UI is ~2,300 lines of JS/CSS/HTML, iOS C++ runner is ~700 lines. That's a new subsystem in languages the project didn't previously ship, and the SUPPORT-MATRIX implies ongoing support. Who owns this after merge?\n\n6. **All CI green** is suspicious given the scope — mobile paths aren't being smoke-tested in CI. Adding at least a lint/syntax-check pass for the mobile installer would catch regressions.\n\n**Recommendation: split into 4 PRs.**\n1. **Installer dispatcher + platform detection** (common.sh, dispatch.sh changes, install.sh shebang). Gets reviewed as an infrastructure change.\n2. **Android Termux preview** (installers/mobile/android-*, android-local-ui/, dream-mobile.sh for Android). Reviewed as a new product surface.\n3. **iOS a-Shell preview** (ios-* scripts + C++ runner + build scripts). Reviewed with emphasis on the binary question.\n4. **Docs + README mobile sections**. Lands after 1-3 are in.\n\nHappy to re-review each piece. The work is interesting and I don't want it to languish, but landing this as one PR hides too many decisions. Thank you for the submission.","submittedAt":"2026-04-18T14:05:37Z","includesCreatedEdit":false,"reactionGroups":[],"state":"CHANGES_REQUESTED","commit":{"oid":"2b1fde6e233bbf20bf6878e7aa9962c6bad1ce85"}}],"statusCheckRollup":[{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-15T00:40:51Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24430276936/job/71373001789","name":"Basic Review","startedAt":"2026-04-15T00:40:47Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Claude Code Review"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-15T00:41:08Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24430276940/job/71373001699","name":"frontend","startedAt":"2026-04-15T00:40:47Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Dashboard"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-15T00:41:13Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24430276951/job/71373001790","name":"powershell-lint (ubuntu-latest)","startedAt":"2026-04-15T00:40:47Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Lint PowerShell"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-15T00:40:52Z","conclusion":"SUCCESS","detailsUrl":"https://github.com/Light-Heart-Labs/DreamServer/actions/runs/24430276955/job/71373001728","name":"linux-smoke","startedAt":"2026-04-15T00:40:48Z","status":"COMPLETED","workflowName":"Matrix Smoke"},{"__typename":"CheckRun","completedAt":"2026-04-1